# PR Documentation to Confluence Workflow

A workflow for documenting PR changes to Confluence. Generates tailored documentation for various stakeholder groups.

## Trigger Pattern
```
<Confluence_Parent_URL> <PR_URL>
```

Example:
```
https://example.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/TEAM/pages/123456/ChangeLogs https://github.com/org/repo/pull/123
```

## Automatic Steps

### 1. Input Parsing
- Extract owner, repo, pull_number from the PR URL
- Extract cloudId, spaceId, parentPageId from the Confluence URL

### 2. PR Information Gathering
```
/github-pr <PR_URL>  # PR metadata, reviews, comments, changed files included (token-efficient)
gh pr diff <PR_NUM>  # Detailed diff (for code-level analysis)
```

### 3. Stakeholder Classification
Use UIAskUserQuestion to confirm the target stakeholder groups for documentation:
- **API Consumer**: API users (external developers, frontend team, etc.)
- **Implementation**: Implementation owners (backend team, code reviewers, etc.)
- **Business**: Business stakeholders (PM, product planners, etc.)
- **Operations**: Operations team (DevOps, SRE, etc.)

### 4. Document Structure Generation
Create a Confluence page with sections divided by stakeholder group:

```markdown
# [PR #{number}] {PR Title}

## Overview
- **PR**: {PR URL}
- **Date**: {date}
- **Author**: {author}

---

## Part 1: {Stakeholder Group 1 Name}

{Include only content relevant to this group}

---

## Part 2: {Stakeholder Group 2 Name}

{Include only content relevant to this group}
```

### 5. Confluence Page Creation
```
mcp__jira__createConfluencePage
- cloudId: {extracted from URL}
- spaceId: {extracted from parent page}
- parentId: {parent page ID}
- title: "[PR #{number}] {title}"
- body: {generated content}
- contentFormat: "markdown"
```

## Document Template Guide

### API Consumer Template
```markdown
## API Changes

### New APIs
| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| /api/v1/xxx | POST | Description |

### Request/Response Examples
```json
// Request
{ ... }

// Response
{ ... }
```

### Breaking Changes
- None / Yes (detailed description)

### Migration Guide
1. Step 1
2. Step 2
```

### Implementation Template
```markdown
## Implementation Details

### Changed Files
| File | Change Type | Summary |
|------|------------|---------|
| path/to/file | Added/Modified | Description |

### Architecture Changes
- New components/services added
- Dependency changes

### Key Logic Changes
1. Change point 1
2. Change point 2

### Tests
- Unit tests: Yes/No
- Integration tests: Yes/No
```

## Output Format

### 📄 Documentation Complete

**Confluence page**: {created page URL}

#### Document Structure
- Part 1: {group name} - {summary}
- Part 2: {group name} - {summary}

#### Next Steps
Use UIAskUserQuestion to confirm additional actions:
- Revise documentation
- Add another stakeholder group
- Done

---

